etymologies: late Middle English. From Anglo-Norman poleter, poletier, pulter, pultere, pulleter, pulletere, pulletier and Old French, Middle French pouletier, Middle French poletier, poulletier from polet, poulet, poullet, pulet, pullet + -er, -ier

definitions: poulterer. Now chiefly in "Poulters' Company": the name of a livery company of the City of London.
